A. HTTP is the protocal used for viewing web pages on the internet.  The “Client” in a  connection is the computer web addresses used by http to view the web pages 
and the “Server” is the computer that is “listening” for calls to come and direct it.
b. it encrypts the data that is being retrieved by http and uses encryption algorithms to scramble the data thats being transferred.
5. a.  Not securing your web browser can lead quickly to a variety of computer problems caused by anything from spyware being installed without your knowledge to 
intruders taking control of your computer.
b. One problem with using ActiveX in a web browser is that it greatly increases the attack surface, or “attackability,” of a system. Installing any Windows application 
introduces the possibility of new ActiveX controls being installed. Vulnerabilities in ActiveX objects may be exploited via Internet Explorer, even if the object was 
never designed to be used in a web browser
